# fix-skill-validation-warnings — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-05-02)

**Changed by:** Session — fix CI failures in PRs #1498 and #1516 (ProjectMnemosyne)
**Verification:** verified-precommit

### What changed

- Updated description to include trigger conditions for wrong Failed Attempts column names and MD033 inline HTML
- Added `user-invocable: false`, `verification`, and `history` frontmatter fields
- Added 2 new When to Use triggers (#6 wrong column names, #7 MD033 angle-bracket placeholders)
- Added new Step 8 with detailed fix patterns for single-skill CI failures:
  - Failed Attempts table required columns (exact 4-column format)
  - MD033 inline HTML from bare angle-bracket placeholders
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows: wrong column names, bare angle-bracket placeholder
- Added Verified On section
- Fixed bare URL in References (MD034 compliance)
- Added markdownlint MD033 reference link

### Why

The existing skill covered bulk validation fixes via automation scripts. A new pattern
emerged: individual skill PRs failing CI due to (1) wrong Failed Attempts column names
and (2) markdownlint MD033 from angle-bracket placeholder text in prose. These are
single-file fixes unrelated to bulk imports, and the exact required column names are
non-obvious (easy to paraphrase incorrectly).

